I cannot comment on the quality of the place because I was not let in. I provided NYID and was asked to pay. Because I denied to pay them extra (which I was not required to do so, they just wanted money for themseleves) they did not let me in and became aggressive. The bouncers at the time were negligent, unlicensed, and crossed the fine line of bouncing that led to battery. They intentionally got aggressive with my boyfriend to instigate an argument. My boyfriend was granted access, they even marked him, when he tried to go in three security rushed up to him and yanked his hand off on the door stating he could not go in AFTER he had paid and was told he was good to go. They yanked his hand with excessive force which turned the prior assault into battery (This place needs better bouncers.) They acted outlandish and egregiously excessive beyond the scope of their duties. (Which again they should not have been working because they were not licensed). The employer will be held liable in addition to the individual security personnel that night.
